# User Profile — &lt;USER_FIRST_NAME&gt;

> Tier-2 persistent memory: identity, people, preferences, goals.
> Stable, slow-changing. Loaded into the system prompt every turn.
> If something here changes more than once a month, it belongs in MEMORY.md or the Sheet, not here.

This is a **sanitised template**. The deployed instance carries a real
`USER.md` with names, card numbers, and goals. Fork this file, fill the
placeholders in, save as `USER.md` in the same directory, and add a
`COPY hermes-config/USER.md /root/.hermes/USER.md` line to your Dockerfile.

